Your project is **MSTest v1** — it uses the old `QualityTools` assembly reference. Here's what to change:

### 1. Replace the assembly reference with MSTest v3 NuGet packages

In `TestProject.csproj`, remove the assembly reference and add the MSTest metapackage:

```xml
<!-- REMOVE this -->
<Reference Include="Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework" />

<!-- ADD this -->
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="3.8.0" />
```

Your `net462` TFM is supported — no change needed there.

### 2. Fix `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` calls

MSTest v3 removed the untyped `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` overload. In `OrderServiceTests.cs`, lines 19–20 use `object`-typed variables, which will fail to compile:

```csharp
// Before (line 13 — double, works but best to be explicit)
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);
// After
Assert.AreEqual<double>(expected, actual);

// Before (line 20 — object, will NOT compile in v3)
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);
// After
Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual);
```

### 3. Timeout behavior

Your `[Timeout(5000)]` on line 26 is fine, but note that v3 unified timeout behavior across runtimes — verify it still behaves as expected after migration.

